quotes.text: This rich-get-richer phenomenon has been documented in scientific fields ranging from physics to economics over the past century. The sociologist Robert Merton called it the Matthew effect, after a passage from the Gospel according to Matthew that did a decent job of describing the concept, albeit with outdated diction: “For unto every one that hath shall be given, and he shall have abundance.” This means that preferential attachment, in basic terms, was evident as far back as biblical times.
